public final class SQLDialectAdjustmentWarning
extends interbase.interclient.SQLWarning

A warning that the value specified in the sqlDialect connection property is not valid for the associated database and the dialect value has been changed.

An attempt to set a connection SQL dialect to negative value or to a value that exceeds the database's SQL dialect may throw this warning. Connection SQL dialects that are too high are adjusted to match the database's SQL dialect. Negative connection SQL dialects are adjusted to dialect 1. A connection SQL dialect of 0 (zero), which is the default, uses the SQL dialect of the database (but no warning is thrown).

// CJL-IB6 change the link to conform // CJL-IB6 perhaps we should delete this class entirely. The error code associated with this warning is always ErrorCodes.unlicensedComponent.
